{{Infobox language |name=Gejia |altname=<big>Ge</big> |nativename=Zhong'an River Miao |states=[[China]] |region=[[Guizhou]] |ethnicity=[[Gejia people|Gejia]] |speakers=60,000 |date=1995 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Hmong-Mien |fam2=[[Hmongic languages|Hmongic]] |fam3=[[Western Hmongic]] |fam4=Chuanqiandian cluster |dia2=Dongjia |dia1=Gejia |iso3=hmj |glotto=geee1239 |glottorefname=Ge }}
The '''Ge''' or '''Gejia''' language ({{zh|[[File:Gě-chinese.svg|18px]]家语}}), also known as '''Chong'anjiang Miao 重安江苗语''', is a [[Miao languages|Miao language]] of [[Huangping County]], Guizhou, China. The endonym is spelled ''Mhong'', though it shares this with [[Huishui Miao]]; it is pronounced {{IPA|[m̥ōŋ]}}, as in the [[Hmong language]]. When speaking Chinese, they call themselves ''Gédōu''.
Gejia is spoken in eastern Guizhou, in speech islands within the area of the [[Hmu language]], which includes the standard dialect.
==Dongjia== The Dongjia (东家) language of [[Majiang County]], Guizhou is related to Gejia. The Dongjia people are officially classified as [[She people|She]], but speak a [[West Hmongic]] language. Their autonym is ''Gameng'' (嘎孟), while the neighboring [[Raojia language|Raojia]] people call them ''Gadou'' (嘎斗). The Dongjia people of Liubao 六堡村, Xingshan Township 杏山镇, Majiang County was studied by Dong Bo (2008). Chen Xueyu (2011) considers Gejia and Dongjia to form two dialects of Chong'anjiang Miao, which belongs to the [[Chuanqiandian]] branch.
==References== {{Reflist}} *http://lingweb.eva.mpg.de/numeral/Miao-Changanjiang.htm *Dong Bo [董波]. 2008. ''[http://cdmd.cnki.com.cn/Article/CDMD-10384-2009080747.htm From Dongjia to She]'' [从东家人到畲族——贵州麻江县六堡村畲族的人类学考察]. M.A. dissertation, Xiamen University. http://www.docin.com/p-467133563.html *Chen Xueyu (2011). [http://cdmd.cnki.com.cn/Article/CDMD-10052-1011166096.htm 论东家话在苗语川黔滇方言中的地位].
