[[File:Gonçal Mayos.jpg|thumb|Gonçal Mayos.]]
'''Gonçal Mayos Solsona''' (born 1957) is a [[Spain|Spanish]] philosopher, essayist and professor at the [[University of Barcelona]]. Specialist by [[Nietzsche]], [[Hegel]], [[Herder]], [[Immanuel Kant|Kant]], [[Descartes]], [[D'Alembert]]..., has evolved into the study of great modern movements ([[rationalism]], [[illustration]], [[Romanticism]], [[philosophy of suspicion]]) and its influence on contemporary [[Postmodernism]]. He chairs the [http://www.ub.edu/histofilosofia/maragall/ Joan Maragall Liceu of Philosophy] of [[Ateneu Barcelonès]] and directs the Open Network for Postdisciplinarity and Macrophilosophy (OPEN-PHI) and the [http://girchenews.blogspot.com.es/ Grup Internacional de Recerca 'Cultura, Història i Estat' (GIRCHE)].

Mayos has cradled the term "macrophilosophy" ([http://www.ub.edu/histofilosofia/gmayos_old/0macrofilosofia.htm "macrofilosofía"]<ref>- G. Mayos, [http://www.ub.edu/histofilosofia/gmayos_old/PDF/macrofilosofiaMod.pdf "Para una macrofilosofía"] en ''Macrofilosofía de la Modernidad'', Roda: dLibro, 2012, pp. 9-16.</ref>) to characterize his overall analysis, comparative, interdisciplinary and long-term processes in philosophical, epistemological, sociological and political fields. He has written numerous books and articles,<ref>http://orcid.org/0000-0001-9017-6816</ref> for example: ''The Society of Ignorance'' (on the occasion of World Day d'Internet, 17.5.2009), A. Brey, D. Innerarity and G. Mayos, foreword by E. Carbonell. Edited by [http://www.infonomia.com www.infonomia.com]. Free Download [http://www.theignorancesociety.com www.theignorancesociety.com] (available in English, Spanish and Catalan).

