The '''Institute of the Estonian Language ''' ({{lang-et|Eesti Keele Instituut}}) is the language regulator of the [[Estonian language]]. It was founded in 1993 as the Institute of Language and Literature was reorganized. It is located in [[Tallinn]]. Its director is currently [[Tõnu Tender]].

