{{Infobox person | name = Paule du Bouchet | image = Paule du Bouchet (SNE) - Grand Prix du livre audio 2015 (18674422350).jpg | image_size = | alt = | caption = Paule du Bouchet in 2015 | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1951|4|19|df=yes}} | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | residence = | nationality = French | education = | alma_mater = | occupation = [[Young adult literature|Youth literature]] writer | years_active = | employer = | organization = | agent = | known_for = | notable_works = | style = | home_town = | television = | religion = <!-- Religion should be supported with a citation from a reliable source --> | spouse = | children = | awards = | signature = | website = <!-- {{URL|Example.com}} --> | footnotes = }}
'''Paule du Bouchet''' (born on 19 April 1951) is a French writer, novelist and author of several books for youth. She is currently in charge of the Music Department of [[Gallimard Jeunesse]].<ref name=Paule>{{cite web |url=http://www.gallimard.fr/Contributeurs/Paule-Du-Bouchet |title=PAULE DU BOUCHET |author=<!--Not stated--> |date=2004-05-18 |website=[[Éditions Gallimard]] |publisher= |accessdate=2018-01-27 |language=fr}}</ref>
== Career == Paule du Bouchet was born on 19 April 1951, daughter of [[André du Bouchet]] and {{ill|Tina Jolas|fr}}, Tina left the poet André and 6-year-old Paule for another poet [[René Char]] in 1957.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.lemonde.fr/livres/article/2011/05/05/emportee-de-paule-du-bouchet_1517173_3260.html |title="Emportée", de Paule du Bouchet : pour l'amour d'une mère... |last=Cahen |first=Didier |authorlink=Didier Cahen |date=2011-05-05 |website=[[Le Monde]] |publisher= |accessdate=2018-01-27 |language=fr}}</ref>
She is passionate about music and pianist. Before working in book publishing, she studied philosophy and music, then she taught philosophy and gave musical training to children. She has been a journalist of the French magazine ''{{ill|Okapi (magazine)|lt=Okapi|fr|Okapi (magazine)}}'' ([[Bayard Presse]]) from 1978 to 1985.<ref name=Picasso>{{cite book |last1=Bernadac |first1=Marie-Laure |last2=Du Bouchet |first2=Paule |translator-last=Jarrín Rodríguez |translator-first=Teresa |date=2011 |title=Picasso: Genialidad en el arte |series=Coll. “[[Biblioteca Ilustrada]]” |volume=8 |url=https://books.google.com/books/about/Picasso.html?id=L-SYZwEACAAJ |location=Barcelona |publisher=Blume Naturart |page=10 |isbn=978-84-8076-934-1 |language=es-ES |quote=About the authors}}</ref> Later she turned her career towards publishing and youth literature. She has written many novels, including ''{{ill|Chante, Luna|fr}}'' in 2004, {{lang|fr|Le journal d’Adèle|italic=yes}} in 2007, {{lang|fr|À la vie à la mort}}, {{lang|fr|Comme un ours en cage}}, et cetera. She currently has published more than 40 works at [[Éditions Gallimard]] and is director of “{{lang|fr|Écoutez lire|italic=no}}” since 2004, a collection of [[audiobooks]] produced by Gallimard.<ref name=Paule /> She was also responsible for the {{lang|fr|Musique}} series of “[[Découvertes Gallimard]]” [[Collection (publishing)|collection]], and was its editor from 1984 to 1996.<ref name=Picasso /><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.babelio.com/auteur/Paule-du-Bouchet/27086 |title=Paule du Bouchet |date= |website={{ill|Babelio|fr}} |publisher= |accessdate=2018-01-28 |language=fr}}</ref> Her book {{lang|fr|Picasso : Le sage et le fou}}, co-written with Marie-Laure Bernadac, from the same collection, was one of the bestsellers in France.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.gallimard.fr/Divers/Plus-sur-la-collection/Decouvertes-Gallimard/(sourcenode)/116085 |title=Collection Découvertes Gallimard |publisher=[[Éditions Gallimard]] |accessdate=2018-01-28 |language=fr}}</ref>
At an interview with ''[[Le Monde de l’éducation]]'', Paule shared her thoughts on youth literature: “Writing for teenagers involves two constraints that on the one hand, a simple expression, a clear writing style, direct without being simplistic; on the other hand, the expression of big questions, profound and existential ones that accompany adolescence and guide us as a lantern in the night –even if we are not aware of it later– in our whole life.”<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gallimard-jeunesse.fr/Livres-pour-enfants-Gallimard-Jeunesse/Auteur/Paule-Du-Bouchet |title=Paule Du Bouchet |author=<!--Not stated--> |date= |website=[[Gallimard Jeunesse]] |publisher= |accessdate=2018-01-27 |language=fr |quote=En savoir plus}}</ref>
== Selected publications == * Co-author with Marie-Laure Bernadac, ''Picasso : Le sage et le fou'', collection « [[Découvertes Gallimard]] » (nº 4), série Arts. Éditions Gallimard, 1986 (new edition in 2007)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gallimard.fr/Catalogue/GALLIMARD/Decouvertes-Gallimard/Decouvertes-Gallimard/Arts/Picasso |title=''Picasso : Le sage et le fou'', collection Découvertes Gallimard (n° 4) |author=<!--Not stated--> |date= |publisher=[[Éditions Gallimard]] |language=fr |accessdate=2018-01-27 |quote=}}</ref> ** UK edition – ''Picasso: Master of the New'', ‘[[New Horizons (Thames & Hudson)|New Horizons]]’ series. Thames & Hudson, 1993 ** US edition – ''Picasso: Master of the New Idea'', “[[Abrams Discoveries]]” series. Harry N. Abrams, 1993 * ''Magnificat : Jean-Sébastien Bach, le cantor'', collection « [[Découvertes Gallimard]] » (nº 116), série Arts. Éditions Gallimard, 1991 * ''Le journal d’Adèle'', collection « Folio Junior » (nº 876). Éditions Gallimard, 1995 (new edition in 2007) * ''À la vie à la mort'', collection « Pôle Fiction » (nº 85). Éditions Gallimard, 1999 (new edition in 2016)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gallimard.fr/Catalogue/GALLIMARD-JEUNESSE/Pole-Fiction/A-la-vie-a-la-mort |title=''À la vie à la mort'', collection Pôle Fiction (n° 85) |author=<!--Not stated--> |date= |publisher=[[Éditions Gallimard]] |language=fr |accessdate=2018-01-27 |quote=}}</ref> * ''Comme un ours en cage'', collection « Folio Junior » (nº 1139). Éditions Gallimard, 2001 * ''Chante, Luna'', collection « Pôle Fiction » (nº 97). Éditions Gallimard, 2004 (new edition in 2016)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gallimard.fr/Catalogue/GALLIMARD-JEUNESSE/Pole-Fiction/Chante-Luna |title=''Chante, Luna'', collection Pôle Fiction (n° 97) |author=<!--Not stated--> |date= |publisher=[[Éditions Gallimard]] |language=fr |accessdate=2018-01-27 |quote=}}</ref> * ''Prince Orpheus'', illustrations by Fabian Negrin, [[J. Paul Getty Museum]] Publications, 2004
