'''Time-late''' is a term used primarily in [[naval warfare]] that refers to the time lag between some datum's generation and actions taken based on it.  In other words, it is something that is not [[Real-time (disambiguation)|real-time.]]

It is often used in the context of a weapon's time of flight: the time between launch and (intended) contact with a target results in a time-late.

